---
import GuideLayout from '../components/layout/GuideLayout.astro';
import StatTable from '../components/ui/StatTable.astro';
import Callout from '../components/ui/Callout.astro';
import JsonLd from '../components/seo/JsonLd.astro';

const headings = [
  { depth: 2, slug: 'races', text: 'Races' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'power-sources', text: 'Power Sources' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'stat-roll', text: 'The Stat Roll' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'starter-armor', text: 'Starter Armor' },
  { depth: 2, slug: 'example-builds', text: 'Example Builds' },
];
---

<GuideLayout
  title="Forging an Identity"
  description="Complete guide to character creation in Ultimate Dominion. Understand races, power sources, stat allocation, starter armor, and optimal build strategies."
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Character Creation' }]}
  headings={headings}
>
  <JsonLd schema={{
    '@type': 'FAQPage',
    mainEntity: [
      { '@type': 'Question', name: 'What races can I choose in Ultimate Dominion?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Human (+1 STR, +1 AGI, +1 INT), Elf (-1 STR, +2 AGI, +1 INT, -1 HP), and Dwarf (+2 STR, -1 AGI, +1 HP).' } },
      { '@type': 'Question', name: 'How do stats work in Ultimate Dominion?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'You have 19 stat points distributed across STR, AGI, and INT (range 3–10 each). Base HP is 18. Stats determine combat effectiveness, item eligibility, and combat triangle positioning.' } },
      { '@type': 'Question', name: 'Does power source matter?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Power source (Divine, Weave, Physical) grants a real bonus at level 5: Divine gives +2 max HP, Weave gives +1 INT, Physical gives +1 extra stat point. It does not restrict your abilities, equipment, or class options.' } },
    ],
    dateModified: '2026-03-12',
  }} slot="head" />

  <h1>Forging an Identity</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary">
    Ultimate Dominion character creation has four steps: choose a race (Human, Elf, or Dwarf — each with permanent stat modifiers), select a power source (Divine, Weave, or Physical — grants a bonus at level 5), roll stats (19 points across STR/AGI/INT, range 3-10 each, with 3 re-rolls), and pick starter armor (Cloth, Leather, or Plate). All choices are permanent and determine your combat effectiveness and equipment eligibility.
  </p>
  <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary/60 mt-2">Last updated: March 2026</p>

  <h2 id="races">Races</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2"><em>Human (+1/+1/+1 balanced), Elf (-1 STR/+2 AGI/+1 INT/-1 HP fast and sharp), Dwarf (+2 STR/-1 AGI/+1 HP tough and strong).</em></p>
  <p>
    Each race grants permanent stat modifiers applied on top of your rolled stats. These cannot be changed later.
  </p>

  <StatTable
    title="Race Modifiers"
    rows={[
      { name: 'Human', str: '+1', agi: '+1', int: '+1', hp: '—', extra: 'Balanced — no weaknesses' },
      { name: 'Elf', str: '-1', agi: '+2', int: '+1', hp: '-1', extra: 'Fast and sharp, but fragile' },
      { name: 'Dwarf', str: '+2', agi: '-1', int: '—', hp: '+1', extra: 'Tough and strong, but slow' },
    ]}
  />

  <Callout type="tip" title="Race choice matters most early">
    At level 1, a +2 modifier is a 20-30% boost to that stat. As you level and acquire items, race modifiers become a smaller portion of your total power — but they never stop mattering for stat thresholds on equipment.
  </Callout>

  <h2 id="power-sources">Power Sources</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2"><em>Divine (+2 HP at level 5), Weave (+1 INT at level 5), Physical (+1 stat point at level 5). Does not restrict abilities or gear.</em></p>
  <p>
    Your power source defines your character's identity — how they explain their abilities to the world. It also grants a <strong>real bonus at level 5</strong>:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Divine</strong> — your strength comes from the remnants of dead gods. Healing and protection. <em>Level 5 bonus: +2 max HP.</em></li>
    <li><strong>Weave</strong> — you tap into raw arcane energy. Pure magical power. <em>Level 5 bonus: +1 INT.</em></li>
    <li><strong>Physical</strong> — no magic, no prayers. Just skill, muscle, and steel. <em>Level 5 bonus: +1 extra stat point.</em></li>
  </ul>

  <Callout type="info">
    Power source does not restrict your equipment, class, or abilities. A Physical character can still use spells. A Divine character can still swing a greatsword. The level 5 bonus is permanent once earned.
  </Callout>

  <h2 id="stat-roll">The Stat Roll</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2"><em>19 points randomly across STR/AGI/INT (3-10 each). Base HP: 18. 4 total rolls (1 initial + 3 re-rolls). Permanent once confirmed.</em></p>
  <p>
    When you create a character, 19 points are randomly distributed across three stats:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Strength (STR)</strong> — physical damage, armor penetration, combat triangle position vs AGI</li>
    <li><strong>Agility (AGI)</strong> — hit chance, dodge chance, combat triangle position vs INT</li>
    <li><strong>Intelligence (INT)</strong> — spell damage, magical resistance, combat triangle position vs STR</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Each stat ranges from <strong>3 to 10</strong>. Your base HP starts at <strong>18</strong>, modified by race.
    You get <strong>4 total rolls</strong> (1 initial + 3 re-rolls). Choose carefully — once you've used your re-rolls, you're locked in.
  </p>

  <Callout type="warning" title="Stats are permanent">
    Once confirmed, your base stats are locked. You'll gain stat points as you level (see <a href="/guide/progression">Progression</a>), but your starting roll sets the foundation.
  </Callout>

  <h2 id="starter-armor">Starter Armor</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2"><em>Cloth (INT builds), Leather (AGI builds), or Plate (STR builds) — each adds stat modifiers on top of your roll.</em></p>
  <p>
    After rolling, you choose one starter armor. Each type shifts your stats further:
  </p>

  <StatTable
    title="Starter Armor Modifiers"
    rows={[
      { name: 'Cloth', str: '-1', agi: '+1', int: '+2', extra: 'Best for INT builds' },
      { name: 'Leather', str: '+1', agi: '+2', int: '—', extra: 'Best for AGI builds' },
      { name: 'Plate', str: '+2', agi: '-1', int: '—', hp: '+1', extra: 'Best for STR builds' },
    ]}
  />

  <h2 id="example-builds">Example Builds</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2"><em>Bruiser (Dwarf+Plate), Shadow (Elf+Leather), Arcanist (Elf+Cloth), Generalist (Human+Leather).</em></p>
  <p>
    Combine race + armor to push a stat as high as possible, or balance across multiple stats. Here are some starting archetypes:
  </p>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 not-prose my-6">
    <div class="guide-card border-l-4 border-red/50">
      <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-sm mb-1">The Bruiser</h3>
      <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mb-2">Dwarf + Plate</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-primary">+4 STR, -2 AGI, +2 HP. Maximum physical damage from turn one. Aim for STR-scaling weapons and heavy armor. Dominates Rogue-class monsters via the combat triangle.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="guide-card border-l-4 border-green/50">
      <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-sm mb-1">The Shadow</h3>
      <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mb-2">Elf + Leather</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-primary">-1 STR, +4 AGI, +1 INT, -1 HP. Extremely evasive. Harder to hit, crits more often. Counters Mage-class enemies. Glass cannon — avoid prolonged fights.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="guide-card border-l-4 border-accent-gold/50">
      <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-sm mb-1">The Arcanist</h3>
      <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mb-2">Elf + Cloth</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-primary">-2 STR, +3 AGI, +3 INT, -1 HP. Maximum spell damage. Crushes Warrior-class monsters. Fragile — needs healing items to survive tougher fights.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="guide-card border-l-4 border-accent/50">
      <h3 class="text-white font-bold text-sm mb-1">The Generalist</h3>
      <p class="text-xs text-text-secondary mb-2">Human + Leather</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-primary">+2 STR, +3 AGI, +1 INT. Balanced with a slight AGI lean. Can equip a wide range of items. Flexible path to any <a href="/guide/classes" class="text-accent">advanced class</a> at level 10.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <Callout type="lore">
    No one remembers who they were before waking in the cave. Race is felt in the bones — an instinct, not a memory. The body remembers what the mind has lost.
  </Callout>
</GuideLayout>
